---
title: One-Pot Beef and Black Bean Chili with Spicy Crema and Monterey Jack Cheese
description: A good chili has well-seasoned beef, creamy beans, and tender vegetables. A great chili, however, has all that and comes together in one pot in under an hour. This chili is one of the greats. And once you take a bite, we can guarantee you’ll agree. Not to mention, these beefy bowls are adorned with some delicious fixings: tangy hot sauce crema and melty Monterey Jack. If you’ve got some on hand, why not crumble up some tortilla chips and sprinkle them on top for a crunch?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pot-beef-black-bean-chili-d2f5e646.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pot-beef-black-bean-chili-5d76b40292f8cd000f15374a-da8e83fd.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-beef-and-black-bean-chili-5d76b40292f8cd000f15374a
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 780 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 53 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 1000 mg
cuisine: Mexican
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced). Thinly slice half the @jalapeño{1}(halved and sliced thinly) into rounds; mince remaining half. 

> TIP: Remove ribs and seeds for less heat.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and minced jalapeño; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%oz}, @Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper to same pot. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir @tomato paste{1.5%oz} into pot. Cook, stirring, until dark red and combined, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @diced tomatoes{14%oz can}, @black beans{1%13.4oz can} and their liquid, @beef stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/4%cup}, salt, and pepper; stir to combine. Bring to a simmer and cook, uncovered, until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn off heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp} and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste; season with salt and pepper. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Divide chili between #bowls{}. Top with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}(shredded), crema, and as much sliced jalapeño as you like.

> Not to mention, these beefy bowls are adorned with some delicious fixings: tangy hot sauce crema and melty Monterey Jack. If you've got some on hand, why not crumble up some tortilla chips and sprinkle them on top for a crunch?